profile_positions.description:
- Assist the Marketing Manager to execute the agreed annual marketing plan;
- Assist the Marketing Manager by liaising with the Head Office Marketing team and network agencies to develop and deliver a communication strategy to support the annual marketing plan, including PR initiatives, TV, local press / radio, outdoor, CRM, website, and sponsorship;
- Coordinating centre events and promotions;
- Coordinate agreed sales and marketing activity for the centre including tenant liaison, internal centre communication, and visual environment to improve communication of a clear brand identity;
- Work closely with the Centre Team, Head Office and Digital Agencies to ensure the Centre websites, Social Media, and Newsletters feature relevant and up to date content providing a smooth user navigation across devices; 
- Updating the websites and creating newsletters with global promotions, news and offers and upload imagery on the websites for each new season;
- Successfully manage the social media channels of the Centre to achieve a strong level of engagement with premium quality content;
- Collaborate with Head Office and Digital agency to manage the Facebook page, ensuring the engagement of current followers and the recruitment of new fans;
- Manage Instagram page and develop engaging content, adhering to style guide;
- Implement data capture and social activity in-Centre to drive database and fan growth;
- Responsible for product photography for local website;
-	Support the Digital Content Process - display banners, websites & Social Media are adhering the guidelines;
- Liaise with Guest Service teams to ensure effective communication and implementation of relevant marketing activities (including customer data capture);
- Supervise and guide trainees in the centre;
- Collate and process marketing financial administration & reports to assist the Marketing Manager in monitoring and reporting on centre marketing budgets.
